replies.body:
Champs can be easy to play without being outdated/cancerous, and high-skill or "modern" doesn't mean having a million dashes. 
Examples of good champs that can be played by beginners, but still fit into modern league, AND have meaningful skill expression: {{champion:103}} {{champion:22}} {{champion:86}} {{champion:51}} {{champion:254}} {{champion:61}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:420}} {{champion:25}} 
Contrast that with very low-skill champs with outdated mechanics that are cancerous to play against or obviously stick out: {{champion:23}} {{champion:9}} {{champion:106}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:90}} AND YES {{champion:24}} {{champion:75}} 

Champs can be easy to pick up without being outdated and unfair. League doesn't need braindead point-and-click champs at all.

And here's some examples of high-skill champs that don't feel oppressively mobile, or rely on incredibly complex mechanics: {{champion:136}} {{champion:432}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:69}} {{champion:41}} {{champion:110}} {{champion:4}} maybe {{champion:163}} {{champion:68}}

Champs can even counter hypermobility in more meaningful ways: {{champion:78}} {{champion:117}} (decision-making) {{champion:45}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:163}}, lotsa tanks.
